      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FANTASTIC SPIKE (4) was never in contention last time after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won by 2.5 lengths at Murray Bridge (30.01) beating Binnaway Warrior in a Grade 4/5 on June 19. Tough to beat if on-song. BLACK CHIP (8) stalked the lead from the inside draw then took over turning and burst clear to score (30.87) at this track in a Invitation over 530m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Sure to measure up. CARE FACTOR (2) produced a moderate effort last time when fifth at this track over 530m behind BLACK CHIP (31.33) in a Invitation. Placed at his previous run. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Cannot be underestimated. MAJESTIC MCLAREN (7) is not to be discarded.",
